Data Structures

Here are the data structures with brief descriptions:
NaClSrpcArgUsed to convey parameters to and from RPC invocations
NaClSrpcChannelThe encapsulation of all the data necessary for an RPC connection, either client or server
NaClSrpcCharArrayArgument data type for passing arrays of char
NaClSrpcDoubleArrayArgument data type for passing arrays of double
NaClSrpcHandlerDescBinaries that implement SRPC methods (servers) describe their services using these structures
NaClSrpcImcBufferThe structure used to provide a buffering layer over the IMC
NaClSrpcIntArrayArgument data type for passing arrays of int
NaClSrpcRpcRemote procedure call state structure
NaClSrpcServiceA description of the services available on a channel
NaClSrpcVariantArrayArgument data type for passing arrays of NaClSrpcArg
pthread_attr_tA structure representing thread attributes
pthread_cond_tA structure representing a condition variable
pthread_condattr_tA structure representing condition variable attributes
pthread_mutex_tA structure representing a thread mutex
pthread_mutexattr_tA structure representing mutex attributes
pthread_once_tA structure describing a control block used with the pthread_once() function
